logic.Calculations

Class RoofRaisedCalc

  • java.lang.Object
    • logic.Calculations.RoofRaisedCalc

  • public class RoofRaisedCalc
extends Object
    This class handles materials needed for a raised roof on the carport. The exposed method returns a PartslistModel with the items, which are then appended to the 'master list' ("bill of materials").
    Author:
    See Also:
    PartslistModel

      • getMaterialsFromlength

        protected PartslistModel getMaterialsFromlength(ArrayList<MaterialModel> materials,
                                                int length)
                                         throws AlgorithmException
        This method takes in an ArrayList of materials and a length, sorts the list and then calculates the amount of the longest material needed to cover the given length. The calculated materials are added to the PartslistModel, which is then returned. The metod was supposed to be able to switch to use the shorter materials in the given list when the remaining length is shorter than the longest material, but that feature has not yet been implemented.
        Parameters:
        materials -
        length -
        Returns:
        PartslistModel
        Throws:
        AlgorithmException

      • addPartslistWithMaterialsQuantity

        protected void addPartslistWithMaterialsQuantity(PartslistModel calcBOM,
                                                 PartslistModel returnBOM)
        This method is used when several partslists containing the same materials are added together, to ensure the quantity is updated correctly and only one MaterialModel is added pr. material. It takes in the partslist calculated by the other methods and the partslist the calling method wants to return.

      • getCladdingMaterialCount

        protected int getCladdingMaterialCount(int totalWidth,
                                       int incline,
                                       int offset)
                                throws DataException
        This method calculates the amount of claddingmaterial needed for a given carport and returns it. The method uses basic trigonometry to calculate the height for each board and checks if the lengt of the board is less than the length of the given material. The amount is increased when the height of the board is greater than the remaining length of the material.
        Parameters:
        totalWidth -
        incline -
        offset -
        Returns:
        int amountMaterial
        Throws:
        DataException
